    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund more specialised NHS aftercare for new mothers",
        "additional_details": "So many new mothers, first time or otherwise, suffer following the birth of their babies; not just emotionally but physically as well. Some issues, which never get caught at the time, can leave women with serious, long-term problems, such as severe back pain, sciatica, heavy scar tissue, anxiety attacks... the list goes on.",
        "background": "The Government should fund the NHS to provide greater aftercare and support for new mothers following the birth of their child/children. This could include PND support, pelvic floor recovery, support and exercise to repair Diastasis Recti, etc",
